content.description: Excellent sport route with two distinct cruxes. Up blasted rock clipping 3rd bolt at first crux, a steep undercling with a foot smear to a finger/hand crack in a buldge. pull the move and place a small cam approx .75 then clip more bolts to second thin crux and bolts to two bolt anchor
content.location: walk left of humpty about 100 feet past broken/gully area to wall.

content.description: starts 10 feet left of unknown 3. goes up blasted rock past drilled hole then left and up a wide arete to two bolt anchor.
well bolted route on mostly good rock. fun line and continuous at grade.
fun and long route, fairly sustained in the 5.10 rating. Seems to keep going and going. The rock is generally good on the route. Definitely worth doing.
content.protection: many bolts, around 13 or 14 to two bolt anchor/chains
content.location: on the large right wall about 100 feet out of the tunnel, first route on that large wall.

content.description: Easy climbing but chossy. Could clean up over time but right now the rock is very suspect.
content.protection: 2 bolts to a two bolt anchor with quicklinks.
content.location: Second route on the right after you get through the tunnel.

content.description: Fun but a bit loose, particularly toward the top.
content.location: first route to the right, immediately as you get out of the tunnel.

content.description: Last route along road. Mostly clean rock with powerful steep moves between 2nd and 3rd bolts and committing moves to bolts. Angles left and up steep crimps and gastons to easier climbing on second half.
content.location: left of womb with a view about 75 feet on last wall in the crag.

content.description: Big pockets and nice edges take you up this mostly vertical face. Crux is getting over the left side of a bulge after the 2nd bolt.
content.location: First route you come to from the parking area that is also for atlantis, just a stone's throw from your car. Bolt line is above a grungy ledge (watch your step) which you can scramble up to, beginning below and slightly right of bolt line. This route is the right most of three routes within the same group of rock.

content.description: Sport line, put up 10-07. Still a little loose to first bolt then rock gets good. clip first bolt while holding hidden pocket, then enjoy a series of pockets, from small to buckets on your way up. two bolt anchor on top. Fun route. great winter route, the sun hits about 9:30 and warms up fast.
content.location: A 3 minute walk from the Atlantis parking! Down the old tunnel road, about 300 feet from the parking look right for the bolts going up the first outcropping of rock. It's the 3rd line you will come to.

content.description: Fun, short line just at the exit of the tunnel.
content.location: Just before you exit the tunnel look for a bolt high up to your left. Start just below that bolt after stick clipping first bolt unless you are super confident. Climb past 1st bolt then use short crack system and face holds to get to 2nd bolt. Rating dependant on the path you take between 1st and second bolt. The further right you go the easier it is. If you want a challenge head straight from 1st to 2nd bolt without venturing right to ledges.

content.description: starts just to the right of rubble pile of small boulders/rocks in road. Up easy but loose rock to ledge, then clip and climb thin face up. move left to crack using medium sized cam then finish at chains.
short dihedral to face and pockets
content.location: Second route along old road, only about 2 minutes from the atlantis parking. The route is about 20 feet right of Rack of Ribs, starts at base of clean, short dihedral to dirty ledge then slightly left on face/pockets.

content.description: short but full value, fun on good rock.
content.location: A 3 minute stroll from the atlantis parking area on the old road. Hang 10 is the 4th route you will come to, just 100 feet past Rack of ribs. Start just below beginning of a sharp arete. Stand up and grab the arete and reach left to clip first bolt. Getting to the 2nd bolt is the crux. After crux you can wedge your knee under the mini-roof and enjoy the unlikely no hands rest, shake out your digits (Hang 10, get it :() and finish on easier rock.

content.description: Sport lines between 45 and 130 feet on rhyolite. The names of some of the routes are unknown but some more recent routes are known. Rock quality is generally good and will continue to improve as climbing continues. A great winter crag since at about 9:30 the sun hits and warms up the rock quite fast. Easily accessed from the Atlantis parking area.
